Result.instDescription: The HEART College of Innovation & Technology (HCIT), formerly Caribbean Institute of Technology, is a tertiary level institution that provides technology based training programmes to support the Technical Vocational Education and Training (TVET) system in Jamaica. HCIT offers a comprehensive range of full-time, part-time and distance/online Information Technology programmes and short courses that cater to Jamaicans from all walks of life and age groups. HCIT operates and offers training from its primary facility at Montego Freeport and its other Satellite Learning Locations across Jamaica. The HCIT’s mission is to advance national development through innovation and technology; fostering entrepreneurship and business development based on a foundation of continuous practice through incubation, internship and production.
